Here are the exact snippets to add a 4th hero class — I'll use **Cleric** (a support-style healer/caster) as the example, but you can rename/reflavor it however you like.

## 1. In `GameEngine.java` — update the class menu and input range

**Find this (inside `setupPlayer()`):**
```java
        System.out.println("\nSelect Your Class:");
        System.out.println("1. Warrior\n2. Magician\n3. Archer");
        int choice = getValidInput(1, 3);
```

**Replace with:**
```java
        System.out.println("\nSelect Your Class:");
        System.out.println("1. Warrior\n2. Magician\n3. Archer\n4. Cleric");
        int choice = getValidInput(1, 4);
```

## 2. In `Player.java` — add the new class stats in `setupClass()`

**Find this:**
```java
        } else {
            this.playerClass = "Archer";
            this.maxHp = 95; this.hp = 95; this.maxMp = 45; this.mp = 45; this.atk = 18; this.def = 6;
            this.critChance = 0.25; this.dodgeChance = 0.20;
            this.skillName = "Steady Shot"; this.skillCost = 12;
            this.ultName = "Arrow Storm"; this.ultCost = 30;
        }
    }
```

**Replace with:**
```java
        } else if (choice == 3) {
