```

## 4. In `Player.java` — add an innate passive, inside `applyInnatePassive()`

**Find this:**
```java
        } else if (playerClass.equals("Magician")) {
            setMp(mp + 5);
            System.out.println("[Innate Passive] Magician recovers 5 MP.");
        }
    }
```

**Replace with:**
```java
        } else if (playerClass.equals("Magician")) {
            setMp(mp + 5);
            System.out.println("[Innate Passive] Magician recovers 5 MP.");
        } else if (playerClass.equals("Cleric")) {
            setHp(hp + 3);
            setMp(mp + 3);
            System.out.println("[Innate Passive] Cleric channels divine grace, recovering 3 HP and 3 MP.");
        }
    }
```

That's it — no changes needed to `executeAttack()` since it already works generically off `skillName`/`ultName`/`skillCost`/`ultCost`, which you set in step 2.
